description: Climb up the slab using crimps, I avoided the ledge out left, but it doesn't really matter that much.

name: House On The Rock
description: Start left hand on good side pull, and right hand on sloping ledge.  Bump up to the arete, then up and left to a jug to top out.

name: The Deep End
description: Fun stuff and good rock.. and a number of variations.. right direct, far left, and they are all about the same difficulty.  Start in the crevasse, matched on a right facing sidepull (see photo).  Just below the diving board rock.

name: Diving into the shallow end
description: Sit starts on a sharp good edge with the right and the left is grabbing a decent hold on an arete. Do a big move to a small pocket and move out left onto awkward and easy moves to the top.

name: Moon Man
description: Start matched on the left side of a prominent sloper rail.  Climb up and out, probably using a high large left foot for the opening moves.

name: Hiphopanonymous
description: Start on two good crimps make one move out left to another crimp. Then throw for the good edge and top it out.

name: Railroad Slab
description: Climb up the slab using the large sloping rail and crimps on the face.

name: Spare Change
description: Start left hand on a low crimp, and right hand on the arete.  Work up the arete to a somewhat tricky topout.

name: The Shield
description: Climb up face using good crimps and some foot trickery.

name: Fatterpillar
description: Start in the crack and trend left up into the arete.

name: Mainline
description: From a sit, right hand on a prominent sloper shelf and left on an edge, climb the center of the slab.  Essentially a sit to To Crimp a Butterfly.. the line up the center of the slab. The opening moves are the crux.

name: To Crimp A Butterfly
description: Start in the crack and trend right working your way through a series of small holds.

name: Bear Country
description: This is a version of the Beautiful and the Bold Project...   Start sitting, left hand on a good side pull, right on an okay sidepull.  Go left around the corner.  I spiraled around the boulder to topout, it seemed a bit safer.

name: Beautiful and the Bold(Project)
description: Proud!  This boulder is big and beautiful.  Could have a couple options:  First, climb the left side following the corner, the other would stay to the right(terrible landing and much harder).

name: Just the Tips
description: Sit start with a right hand crimp barely big enough for the tips of your fingers. Crank on the start hold to get established on your toes and proceed to climb up the center face of the short slab. The aretes are off.

name: Pins and Needles
description: Start low on left arete of boulder with very low right hand undercling, and left hand around the arete on a thin but sharp crimp. Make moves along holds on the arete through the name sake hold to gain a good crimp on the face. Rock a high foot to roll over the arete to some easier but unprotected climbing to the top.

name: Chasing Daydreams
description: Start low and left on a jug with a big foot hold and with a right crimp. Pull the roof and throw to a jug.

name: Direct to Video
description: Get established on big eye feature on slap.  Balance your way up to the right to sloping jug.  Work the arete and top-out.

name: Dirty Jugs
description: Start with a right hand crimp and a good left hand side pull. Make some easier moves straight up the face. The crux is getting over the lip onto the slab. Probably best not to fall at this point.

name: Double Edge Sword
description: Start sitting with you left hand on a good down pulling ledge, and right on a low pinch on the face.  Squeeze up the tall pillar.  This is just left of Liger.

name: Fish & Gritz
description: Climbs the obvious crack in the corner. Start under the roof on two good finger locks. Sink some super fun jams through the low roof into some easier but more committing moves to the top.     The top is a bad place to fall, but you can bail onto the opposing slab pretty easily if things get sketchy...    Gave it 4 stars because the movement was so fun... Maybe deserves less because of the goofy landing situation...

name: Geometridae Style
description: Offwidth. Start with feet on an obvious mini-ledge just inside the crack. It's your last 'foot' for a while so savor it!About halfway up, a break in the face provides some very good holds to assist in the rest of the kneebar elbow parade. There is a 5-star hand jam towards the top to help prepare for a top out. The top out is tricky and falling would be hard to protect. It is however possible to bail onto the tree if necessary.

name: Horny Toad
description: An eliminate to some extent, but really cool movement..   Start sitting on a right facing sidepull (Same start as Toad Princess). Climb straight up, not using the big ledge right.

name: Iron Jesus
description: Start sitting in the corner of the room.  Climb up and leftward, encountering a shoulder intensive crux sequence.  Move left above the beginning of Oval office, wrap around the arete, and follow the airy top out of Oval office.  Really fun and 20 plus moves.

name: King Crab
description: Start sitting, with a left sidepull seam, and a right undercling.  Climb up the tall face.  The first few moves are the crux, the finish is fairly serious.  Named after an incredible pinch hold that's used.

name: Le Freak
description: Start low on a large jug and climb directly up the face using larger sidepulls.

name: Liger
description: Start sitting, matched on an edge.  Climb up the beautiful and tall arete.

name: Momentum
description: Starts on a left crimper and a right slopey dimple and follows the right arete.

name: Monorail
description: Start on a good low jug on the right side of the face in the hole.  Trend leftward across the face and once you wrap the corner you have sent.

name: Night Train
description: Start as for Monorail (with a jug on the arête) with Liger and Double Edge Sword at your back.  Climb the tall face and continue onwards to the summit via the airy and easy slab.  Really good, probably one of the best of the grade in the park!

name: Oval Office
description: Start crouched in the pit, with your right hand on a triangle pinch, and left on a low incut sidepull.  Climb up and left.  Move left around the arete on pretty good holds to top out high above a jumbled landing.

name: Pull Down Not Up
description: Start on two good edges and work you way up jugs to fun top-out.

name: Reaching For Daylight
description: Start low on a left hand jug and a higher right crimper. Climb up the outer part of the overhang arete onto several well deserved jug rails above.

name: Toad Princess
description: Start sitting on right side of face matched on right facing sidepull.  Trend low and left, gain the arete, then top out.

name: The Uninviting
description: Crux is near the beginning. 2-3 pads is sufficient protection. Moves are good but dab factor decreases quality.

name: Blade Runner
description: From a sit, matched on a sloper, climb the overhanging blade feature. Other walls and boulders are not used.

name: Bottoms Up
description: A low start to Power Bottom starting with the two obvious far edges in the same seam as the OG start holds of Power Bottom.  Probably establish on the wall by facing out and getting a toe hook on the lip.

name: Fully Charged
description: Start with slanting jug right of Real Power.  Climb the tall arête with the hardest moves being low, though the top is thin and you are definitely still climbing.  The landing is not good for a fall up high, be careful! You can pull on from a neighboring boulder and work any of the moves.

name: Mike's Boulder
description: Start under boulder with right hand undercling and left on crimp.  Bump to edge and toss out left for good hold.  Swing your feet up and make your way right to jug.  Top-out.

name: Paula Abdul
description: Sit start with two large side-pulls.  Hike feet and mantle into the face.  The goal is to gain the upper sloper and stand up to the top.  Very Tricky.

name: Power Bottom
description: Start on two good head height edges under the roof.  Do a couple of powerful moves to reach the lip and top out.  This is a lower start to the problem "Take a Stand".

name: Power Hour
description: To the right of Power Bottom in the roof.  From a stand I started crossed, w/ right hand on a blocky pinch, and left on a false grip undercling down and right.  Use tension to climb out the roof and finish on the big slab.

name: Power Ranger
description: Start on slanting jug right of roof (same as Fully Charged).  Trend left and finish as for Power Bottom and Real Power.

name: Real Power
description: This is the low start to "Power Hour" and the real line on the right side of the boulder.  Start low on a left hand undercling and a right hand crimp / pinch and make a big move (Nic), use some toe hook wizardry (Peter), or something else (???) to gain the rail on "Power Hour."  Top out on that problem.

name: Replicant
description: An aesthetic, unlikely looking, slope fest knife feature just next to Blade Runner.Start from a sit, right with an incut jug and left underclinging the blade.  Climb straight up through slopey holds with balance, and toss to gain better holds.  Mantle and climb into the trees.Note: the fall is pretty good but a spotter is a good idea.  It wouldn’t be good to miss the landing zone.

name: Take a Stand
description: Amazing Boulder!  This is the stand start to what could be a couple really hard roof lines.    Reach up and grab good edge with left hand and right hand goes up to a crimp at the lip.  Hike feet and get up to jugs over lip.  Upper slab is a bit tricky so heads up.

name: Vinny's Addition
description: Lower start to Mike's Boulder.   Right hand is on undercling, but your left hand starts lower down on small edge.  Make a couple of desperate moves to link into Mike's Boulder.

name: Warm-up
description: Start in middle of boulder on good jugs, and climb up steep face on large holds.

name: Another Nice Arete
description: Climb left arete of nice clean boulder.

name: Bone Saw
description: Physical and full body feature climbing.. Start left hand gaston pinch, and right lower, opening the elevator door on a fin.  Gain the arete and continue up.  A slopey crimp in the face and a knee scum or two could be helpful.

name: Dumpster Diving
description: Dumpster Diving sits on the northwest corner of the boulder.  Start on the right side of a small alcove on two sidepulls and move up through a gaston and a sloper.  Finish out left on the big ledge.

name: Easy Pickings
description: Start on great crimper jugs and thin feet in the middle of the face. Head straight up. Feet and hands near the left arete are off. If you're tall, you can reach for the top in one move after getting feet up high. Others will use a small intermediate crimper.

name: Juggy Ledges
description: A nice little small one.. B side.   Start matched on the arete, gain juggy ledges then get to the top.  Kinda cool. The start is the crux.

name: Little Fingers
description: Little Fingers is on the East side of the boulder.  Start on the ledge and go up on big holds.

name: Oscar the Grouch
description: Start as for Dumpster Diving with underclings sitting.  Climb straight up the arête not moving left to the big shelf.  Good fun.

name: Rhoads Rage
description: Rhoad Rage is the obvious arete on the Southwest corner of the boulder.  Great warmup.

name: Rhoads Rash
description: The face directly to the right of Rhoads Rage.  Some holds may have broken off of the face as a dead rotten tree was leaning up against it when the problem was first found.

name: Roger Rabbit
description: From a sit on the right, follow the arête/ sloper feature left through thin holds to the end of the feature and top out.

name: Weekly Pickup
description: Start just right of Dumpster Diving. Sit start using underclings for both right and left hands. Make a tuff move to a right sidepull. Figure out how to get onto the slab. Top it out.    The right arete is most definitely off.

name: Eagle Eye
description: Hard sit start on left side-pull and right with large undercling pinch.  Hike right foot and dead-point good edge.  Top-out.  Really fun climbing.

name: Step up to the plate
description: Stand start with ledge, and throw for the lip.  Top-out.  Could be more variations on this boulder aswell.

name: The Futballer Direct
description: Start in middle of face and get to break in middle.  Adjust to double under-clings with tricky feet and hit upper crimp, top-out.

name: The Futballer
description: Tricky start.  Climb left side of face and hanging corner to gain good crimp up high, top-out.

name: Half Dome Corner
description: Start low on right crimp and left hand pinch feature under roof.  Gun up for some good holds on the corner and campus around to the right.  Follow the lip and top-out above the HD project.

name: Pine Needle Arete
description: Climb up the arete on right side of boulder.

name: Regular Route
description: Amazing boulder!  You can probably guess where the name stems from.  Start low on ok edges and reach sharp flake.  Set your feet and make a big bump move to good edge.  Top-out.  Could be an even lower start.

name: Snake Dike
description: Start at chest-high large triangular hold, climb up arete to top out.

name: All the Girls Say
description: Starting low on the right side of the roof on edges next to each other, pull on and move leftward through slopes, pinches, and and edge or two.  Top out left of the ferns, and it is a little tricky.  The first few moves are dabby, but the holds and movement is very good..

name: Archangel
description: A real gem, likely one of the best for the grade around.  From a stand climb the shield like face and double arete feature. The top is a bit committing but it does pad up well.

name: Blind Faith
description: Start sitting, left hand low on a ledge with a pocket on the left side, and right on the arete on a spot with a little edge.  Smack up the arete, and once you are standing up it is pretty much done.  It has been topped out various ways.  If you start with a left sidepull a couple moves in it’s probably a grade easier.

name: Burial
description: Sit start on a large underling jug, grab an edge, and do a big move to a good hold. From the good hold is excellent V0 climbing to a big ledge you can escape and stand onto. Up to this point is a V2, but continuing straight up from the ledge adds a grade and puts you high off the ground in a no fall zone. The top is super fun but the added difficulty and height make it for the non faint of heart. Do whatever gets you psyched, this is an excellent climb.

name: Eternal Punishment
description: One of the best at the lake; classic anywhere. Sit starts on an obvious juggy rail. Crux is the first two moves, where you likely are going to do a big move to a crimp and then jump to a jug. From here the difficulty eases up but the landing isn't great and its not easy to pad. Originally done topping out straight up above the start but the far more natural line is traversing right as soon as you can at the top(topping out direct doesn't change difficulty but topping out this way makes it an X).

name: Eternal Return
description: Logical linkup between Heaven's gate and the top of Eternal Punishment. Start in the same position as Heaven's Gate and climb straight up and traverse to the right to the jugs on Eternal Punishment. Continue topping out like on Eternal Punishment. Fun moves, not nearly as good as either of the original lines but worth doing if in the area.

name: Halo
description: Start sitting on the rock, squeezing the obvious feature.  Squeeze your way up and top out.  A good spotter is key.

name: Heaven's Gate
description: One of the best in Wisconsin; A five star boulder anywhere. Heaven's Gate is a long power endurance boulder that follows a natural traverse line climbing most of the boulder(Should be noted that there's possibility for a direct top out variation although it may be more contrived, harder, and definitely more dangerous than this line). There is no super defined crux, but the move to the last good hold before you top out has some difficulty and a fall from this position would be quite dangerous. Starts on a large rail low and to the right.

name: The Red Room
description: Starts sitting on jugs, climbs out a mini roof on quality holds and movement. Crux is moving to the lip, landing is a little weird and you definitely want to pad the rock to the left for the top.null

name: Ripple Prow
description: Fun boulder! Sit start with a right underling and left hand on a gaston, do a couple moves and top out. A knee bar pad may help you out on this one...

name: Ripple Roof
description: Start standing on good holds in the horizontal break. Pull the small roof and work right to top out.  A sit start was also done, which probably adds two or three grades and subtracts two or three stars.

name: Unforgiven Sins
description: Start sitting in the hole, with an incut undercling for the left and a juggy sidepull on the arete for the right.  Climb the face through sustained climbing and some tricky moves.

name: Battleship
description: Start Left hand on a downpulling sloper down and right from the Jenga start hold and right hand down and right under the roof on a pockety sidepull.  Compress your way up and finish on Hungry Hippos.  A really fun hard problem.

name: Collision Course
description: Start as for Jenga and climbing into Falling to Pieces and finish as for that problem.  A tough and wild linkup that is clearly very forced.

name: Down and Dirty
description: Awesome 15 foot roof offwith in a cave.    Start by laying on your back and throwing your feet into the crack at the lowest point in the roof, about 15 feet into the cave. Climb the wide crack going through a couple of rocks that are stuck in the crack (they are on). When you reach the end of the crack, climb the cruxy roof to gain the jugs at the point. Continue on good holds to the top.    You may need to take a couple of minutes to clean out roots and debris that like to gather in the crack.

name: Falling to Pieces
description: Start left hand on good edge from Jenga on the arete, jump to decent right hand crimp, and go up to topout.

name: Hungry Hippos
description: Start with right hand on good edge and left hand on the upper sloper of Jenga.  Set feet and work your way up and right to gain good jug.

name: Hungry Hungry Hippos
description: Start on Jenga and move into the stand start of Hungry Hippos.  It turned out to be a surprisingly natural line with really cool movement.

name: Jenga
description: Start down left on obvious jug, and work your way out right to corner and up to top. The Double heel hook works great to hold yourself on.

name: Jenga Low
description: Left hand on a down pulling sloper down and right of the Jenga start hold and right hand below the roof on a pockety sidepull.  Do a few extra fun moves into Jenga.

name: Monopoly
description: At the Jenga Boulder and looking for something to do?  You are probably standing next to this. Start sitting in the little roof, right hand on a pinch, left on a low fin.  A heal toe cam could be useful.  Gain the lip and probably move left a little to finish.

name: Rockjack
description: SDS at lowest point (corner closest to Jenga) with high heel hook. Traverse left and up to a tricky mantle top-out.    A good warmup for the harder routes in the area.

name: Animated Hands
description: Starts on a sharp left hand crimp and a good right hand undercling.  Move through sloping lip holds to the topout.

name: The Choice
description: Climb up boulder using three options(All V0).  Climb up using both cracks;  Climb up just center crack; or climb up left side with crack and arete.

name: The Duke
description: Start the same as the Dutchess but move up and right around the arete on cool holds.

name: The Dutchess
description: Start left hand on a pinch and right on a good undercling.  Go up and left through a sharp crimp.

name: Empty Space
description: Start on a good left hand sidepull and a crimp for the right and climb some fun, engaging moves up a cool face.

name: Loompa Land
description: Start matched on a good low sidepull and do some tensiony moves up a series of sidepulls.

name: Wonka Crack
description: Climb large crack on south face of boulder.  The right side of the crack is actually a large detached block(little loose).  Reach into the crack and you can lay-back off the block.

name: Iron Man
description: Start as for Megaman, climb into Link to the Past and finish as for that line.  Dabby but fun.

name: Link to the Past
description: Start with right hand pinch and left hand side-pull.  Yard up to crimp and gun for sloper.  Really fun movement.

name: Mega Man
description: Start low on corner of boulder.  Get high heel hooks and lock-off to sloper.  From there find face holds and power up to top.

name: Magnum PI
description: Start on slanted foot chip and side pulls. Great moves up the center of this great boulder.

name: Moo Stache
description: Sit start hugging the arete on two edges and move up through cool moves, one sharp crimp and an odd topout.  Cool line. Was originally done two moves in but the logical start is down low.

name: P.Stachio
description: Start on a good right hand crimp and a left hand pinch and move up the prominent pillar.  Squeeze your way up and throw for the good jug at the top.  Committing last move!

name: Railroad Spike
description: Start on a blocky jug on the left arete of the boulder and move up slopers to a jug.  Sadly, just when it starts to get interesting, it ends.      Either way it's a fun problem on true slopers, kind of a rarity at DL.  Could be easier.

name: Snoop Dog
description: Start on the beginning of Rail Road Spike on left side of boulder and move across lower portion of boulder through tricky and powerful moves into the finish of Moo Stache.

name: A Deeper Understanding
description: A B side and possibly rarity..Start crouched, right hand with a small undercling and left a foot above on a glassy crimp.  Climb the wave-like face.  The start and first move are definitely the crux.

name: Bidness Project
description: Start on the crescent shaped sidepull and go up on miserable holds to a bad sloper.  Looks very hard.

name: Book of Glass
description: Climb up book-cove dihedral on boulder just in front of the Super Slab.  This is actually really fun, and much easier than expected. Go get after it, it's worth it!

name: From a Sit
description: Start low on left side-pull and right on lip.  Traverse left along lip to cool mantle top-out.

name: Intrinsic Design
description: Start sitting below the arete, kind of in the corridor, matched on an edge.  Climb the arete.  The opening move is definitely the crux.

name: Just Grab It!
description: Start with good holds low, and using smart foot work, gain small left crimp and throw for jug out right.  Top-out follows lip up and left.

name: The Last Unicorn
description: Start from a crouch with your right hand on a bump on the arete, and left on a sidepull (the higher friendly one).  Do a hard first move to the lip then trend right and finish as for Moj.  IMO one of the best and fun real hard boulders in the state.  This was envisioned by Steve Schultz and friends when Moj was first put up and took some effort to get done.

name: Minotaur
description: A pretty darn cool one..Start standing with sloper, crimpy pinches.  Maybe set a toe hook and bust left to a better hold.  Possibly gain a crimp and another toe hook and gain a good hold up and right.  Trend left through a seam on pretty good holds, and quest up and left around the corner up a tall and easing slab.

name: Moj
description: This thing is rad!  Start low on left, establish left hand pinch and stab out right to good edge.  Keep you core tight and get feet set to bump your left hand to the finish.

name: More Cowbell
description: A good line but intimidating! Start sitting on the ledge. Right sidepull, left pinch. Punch up left to an incut, somehow gain a ledge system out left, then trend more left to a cruxy finish. The end is actually quite safe.Also has been done matched on the right sidepull and maybe a better, slightly more difficult start.  See what you think.

name: Oklobzija's Problem
description: Start on tiny holds and do a very hard move to the lip and TOP OUT!   This was the Hemarhoads project.

name: Piecemeal
description: SDS on two pod edges near the back of the short cave. Tricky moves on good holds lead to the lip. Trend a bit left for the top out.

name: Pulling on Glass
description: Start on good juggy side-pull and gun up for good edges and top-out.

name: Purple Dragon
description: Start right hand on a sloper on the lip with a chip out of it and left hand on a nice side pull in the overhanging face and climb the boulder.  Cool slopers and some good tenuous moves.  This is a stand to the Corner Project.

name: Purple dragon low
description: Start left hand on sidepull and right hand on the arete.  Find some bad feet and go to the lip!    Later edit: see video

name: The Reaper
description: SDS matched on the obvious rail in the raised alcove. Consistent and powerful moves lead out of the overhang. This thing stays on you until the very end. An exceptional problem.Note: This differs from "More Cowbell" in that after hitting the good hold on the left arete, continue directly up the overhanging face rather than turning the corner and topping out the slab.

name: Reefers Arete(Super Slab Right)
description: Climb up the far right side of Super Slab.  Fun bouldery start leads to a committing battle with the arete.

name: Sticky Icky
description: Starts on the left side of the seam on sidepulls and goes up through another edge to the top.

name: Super Slab
description: Find a good way up the middle of slab using edges and side-pulls.  This thing is super fun, the face is huge and loaded with options.

name: Super Slab Left
description: On left side of slab, climb up crack system using anything you can, Tricky!

name: Super Slab Warmup
description: Very easy warmup route in the super slab area. very fun, especially for newcomers who are new to outdoor bouldering.

name: Clear Cut
description: Climb straight up the short & steep feeling face via nice edges.

name: Tree Hugger Arete
description: Start on lower right side of boulder and climb up arete to a committing finish.   Someone must have done this before, it's really a lot of fun.

name: Tree Hugger Direct
description: SDS with right hand on undercling and left on sharp crimp, toss out right to lip and top-out.

name: The Bear's Den
description: Start on right side of overhang on good ledges and side-pull, traverse out left to slopey but positive holds and finish up on left side of boulder.  Really fun problem with interesting heel hooks and foot swinging action.

name: Brie
description: On the left side of this boulder.  Interesting start holds, a left hand pinch and good right crimp.  Trick your way up the face on bad feet and small holds.

name: Chubby Bunny
description: Start low with good side pulls, paste feet and work your way up featured boulder.  Lots of good movement on this one.

name: Green Corner
description: Climb up the corner coming out a pit.  There's a nice undercling down low that would be cool to start on but it's a bit cramped and there are 0 feet.  We started matched on the next hold (see photo)    It could use some serious brush work on all the lichen.  I lost our brush in the deep chasm beneath the boulder.

name: The Mountain Goat
description: SDS near right side of steep face.  Crank up and out on steep lip to top-out.

name: Sharp Cheddar
description: Up the middle of this overhanging face.  Start as low as you can with absurdly high foot, and crimp your way painfully to the top.  Starts in the pit.

name: Swing State
description: Start with both hands matched on the sharp arete, traverse right through the cave and top out through a hole about 10' over.

name: Tonsillitis
description: This boulder problem starts with your left hand in a crack on the left side of the arete and your right hand on the obvious jug on the right side of the arete. from there make your way up the boulder on balancy moves and top out at the peak of the arete. fun and beautifully located.

name: Wrong Way on a One Way
description: At first look this line looks like it should be pretty easy but with only low left hand holds and the cramped quarters. High step with your right and throw for the slopey rail.

name: Dark Hallway
description: Start sitting right of World War Z, left hand in a flexy undercling that is seemingly solid and right out on a pinch.  Move up and right through the face and top out on the arete to the right.

name: Ground Zero
description: Start as for World War Z but instead of traversing up and to the left, continue straight up the boulder over an intimidating landing and a tricky lip encounter. Once fully on the slab, the climb eases up significantly, but it is a no fall situation...

name: Prowling Turtle
description: A cool boulder worth checking out.. especially if you’re in the area.Start sitting with an obvious undercling feature.  Climb up the overhanging face, likely using a couple of awesome slopers and top out on better holds.

name: Snapper Stew
description: SDS high on two compressing rails and climb straight up the short overhanging block.

name: World War Z
description: Worth seeking out, start sitting with obvious big ledge for your hands.  Trend left through the overhanging face via prominent ledges and mantle with a juggy undercling probably helping a lot.

name: Zombie in the Corner
description: Start standing with sidepulls on either side of the arete in the corridor at head height.  Climb the arete avoiding the dab factor.

name: Black Sheep
description: Starts low under roof and move up to to large feature and move right to lip and top out. There are hold all the way to the lip.

name: Can We Cane 'Em?
description: Start on lower two holds move up to side pulls on lip to move left to top out. Super good traverse.

name: Flower Power
description: Start on left of two crimps with right hand and left hand on slope side pull. Climb out left of roof and top out.

name: Top-Off
description: Start under roof with hands squeezing each side.  Slap out left and then move right up corner.  This is actually really fun and a good little warm up.      I broke off the top finishing jug and took a nasty fall, hence the name.  Good and clean now.

name: Walking Stick
description: Start sitting on the right side of the face on the can we cane'em Boulder.  Traverse the lip all the way to the left arête.  More or less an extension to Can We Cane 'em.  Full value and quite safe.

name: Yo Shorty
description: One move wonder!! Start on two crimps and pop to sloper over the lip. The Gentlemen was hitting the hold.

name: Beautifully Ordinary
description: Started right hand in the crack and left on the smiley hold on the left face.  Follow the crack on large holds to an easy topout.  Great warmup on comfy holds.

name: Bestest Of The Midwestest
description: Start on the large sloper and go straight up to a very comfy jug.

name: The Fire Down Under
description: Start low on underclings and move up to edges along arete.  Make a big move to a jug and top-out.

name: Hurricane
description: Start compressing arete with right hand on nice side-pull and left on corner.  Go straight up!

name: Lil Nuggie
description: Start left hand on the left arete and right on a positive sidepull. Follow positive holds to a slightly sloping topout.

name: Order Of Attack
description: Sit start squeezing either side of the arete and after a tricky first move, trend toward the right on crimps to the topout.

name: Pigment Party
description: Start on the flat sandstone edge and work your way up and left through the juggy rail to a slightly awkward topout.  Can also be done starting on the left and connecting midway through.

name: Silence Of The Bunnies
description: Starts on the obvious jug and follows the right arete to an enjoyable topout.  Great warmup on comfy holds.

name: Sub-Optimal Success
description: Start on the chockstone to the right of the crack and transition onto the large step.  Mantle and topout.

name: Zoo Full Of Defective Animals
description: Start on a flat edge down and left of the large boulder that makes up the landing.  Climb up and right through the prominent arete with long pulls between large breaks.

name: A Little Choss
description: Start matched on the low shelf and move up to the angled shelf. Continue up and left on jugs to top out the boulder.

name: A Little Moss
description: From a sit follow the sandstone jugs up the face. Stay off the quartzite to the left and top out

name: A Little Sauce
description: Start sitting on the angled boulder, facing the corner with hands matched low in the crack. Step onto decent feet and make a big move to good holds on the horizontal. Switch your stance and use the arete to top out.   This is a detached block and although solid, one day it will fall. Pulling on it during the topout creates an uneasiness that either adds or takes away from the climb, depending on your outlook that day

name: Into the Fire
description: This is a detached block roof feature that looks intimidating but climbs great. You'll encounter a juggy arete for one hand, great underclings for the other, and a sloping platform for feet to keep the tension. Stick in a kneebar or heel hook, reach the hold on the face, finish the easy top out, and smile! There are still good problems to be found at the lake :-)

name: Out of the Frying Pan
description: This is an extension of the roof climb, Into the Fire. Left of the roof, start low on the small arete with hands on the shelf and a heel around the arete. Move up to a stand on decent crimps then traverse right and climb Into the Fire. This line extends the pump factor while adding  movement and a more defined start to an already fun climb.

name: All Power, No House
description: Sit start on obvious sidepulls and do a really fun bounce move to a positive edge up high.  Follow techy feet to an easy topout.

name: The Bubbler
description: Start left hand on a positive sidepull, right on a low jug.  Climb up the pillar on holds that are somehow slopier than you expected.

name: Dreamo
description: Start with your right hand on the brick pinch on the arete, left on the good side pull.  Climb engaging moves up phenomenal holds to a fun and exciting finish move.

name: Dreamy Bulge
description: Start on left side of boulder, work your way up to break and climb slopey bulge at top.

name: Fire Chasers
description: Start right on jug rail.  Move up and left along featured corner.

name: Kitten Mittens
description: Start on the obvious jugs in the crack and follow the crack up and left to a positive topout.

name: Obsidian Nightmare
description: Start on a great jug for your left and a positive sidepull for your right.  After a couple of easier intro moves, navigate through a tricky section to reach positive holds on the right side of the arete.

name: Short and Sweet
description: Start with good holds and climb steep face to fun top.

name: Alexander the Moderate
description: Start on the obvious flat hold and go straight up.

name: Fern Gully
description: Start in the crack and go straight up.

name: Lil Sebastian Memorial Arete
description: Start on the obvious jug and go straight up.

name: Pack Your Sewing Machine
description: Start on a good blocky hold down low and work your way into the finger crack.

name: Dyno
description: Start low on jugs, and gain slopey hold for the left hand.  From there hike feet and dyno for the lip.  Super fun!   See pictures on previous page.

name: Fern N Burn
description: Start on the large hold and go straight up the good holds.

name: Fire road five
description: Powerful little problem. Sit start on a small left crimp that you can pinch the side of and a small right side pull. Stick finger slot and move up and left towards the top.

name: Middle Line
description: Mantle on big ledge and balance your way up through crimps and thin crack.  Top-out.   See pictures on previous page.

name: PDS
description: Start on the triangular jug and go straight up.

name: Right Arete
description: Start with obvious edges and work your way up arete.  Fun!

name: Bordeaux
description: Start from a stand on pads, left on a crimp sidepull with a thumb catch and right pinching the heck out of the arete just to the right.Pick a foot, and with difficulty and maybe a slight hop off the pad to get going, gain holds above and top out the arete.An elegant, pure and hard boulder with a distinct crux.  Shorter folks may need to stack pads.The sit or a lower start will be very difficult but it probably is all there.Also worth noting, jump start with right hand on the pinch for v9 probably.

name: Bud White
description: Sit down start of Smooth Operator.    Start on slopey ledge down and right of the start to SO.  Bump out left to crack and get into the start of SO.  Top out same as SO

name: Catch Me If You Can
description: Start right hand in juggy hold and left hand low on a sprag like pinch sitting on a boulder and trick up the mini overhang onto the slab above.  Kind of a funny little problem that turned out to be quite scary due to the poor landing and potential to have a bad fall down the hill into the talus.  Some tricky moves.  Not amazing but maybe worth checking out if you're in the area.

name: Corner Store
description: From a sit climb the square cut arête.

name: Dirty North
description: Start hugging both aretes just right of the tilted project and go straight up, staying on the face.

name: Funk Show Brother
description: Start sitting with a left side pull and right slope.  Bust a tough move right then press/ mantle your way up.

name: The Gift
description: A nice short arete climb with a couple cool moves.  Sit start on 2 good deep crimps that are side by side to the left of the arete.

name: Le Craguette
description: A fun and sweet feature very close to the car, definitely worth checking out. This faces the parking lot, I’m surprised it hadn’t been noticed. Sit start with a gaston for the right and a low spot on the arete for the left.  Climb rightwards along the arete and mantle on good holds.

name: Licking the Weasel
description: Same start as 'What Up Weasel'. Reach the good left hand above the lip (just as in What Up Weasel, see photo) then grab good right hand (underside of overhang) and launch for the prominent arete.  Work your way back (climbers) left up the arete avoiding the tree and topping out.

name: Mini Cooper
description: Start with a down pulling pinchy hold and a small gaston just next to it.  Gain a gaston and finish it up. 3 moves with my method.  Maybe a 1 star Boulder but a decent landing and easy access makes it cooler?

name: North by Northwest
description: From a stand with a ledge, climb the tall arete.  Pads and spotters recommended.  Tall and committing near the top.

name: The One and Only
description: Start low matched on good undercling.  Work you way up and out boulder using foot trickery and raw power.  Lots of holds and really fun movement!   This problem would be 3 to 4 stars if the top-out wasn't so dabby.

name: Sir Mix Alot
description: Starting right hand on jug and left hand on a cool pinch old on the arete, climb out the steep arete doing some awesome and fun moves then do an interesting topout above the boulder.

name: Smooth Operator
description: Stand start with good side-pulls and work your way up left to slopey arete, finish the slick top-out.  Super cool.

name: Smooth Roof Project
description: Start under a bulge and work up poor features to an easy topout.

name: Spit out the Seeds
description: Start with left hand on sharp crimp and right on ok edge by corner.  Throw up a left heel-hook and matle up to good holds.  Tricky!

name: The Strike
description: Start on a side pull nub on the arete and a good right hand. Pull hard into rails on the right and bump up the slopy arete on the left. Do your best not to dab on the tilted boulder and work some magic to move over the bulge. Once standing on the bulge, walk off down the tilted boulder.

name: Suck on the Juice
description: Start low under boulder with left hand on sharp crimp and right on large pinch under roof.  Bump your hands up the right corner of boulder and top-out.

name: Tilted Boulder Slab
description: Climb up slab face on north side of Tilted Boulder.

name: Tilted Face Project
description: Pull on to the face, with a bitey right side pull left of the arete for the right hand, and an undercling for the left.  Establish, probably fire to a sloper on the lip then move right to the arete and finish it up.

name: Tilted Sloper Project
description: From the left, trend right along the lip through cool and bad holds and finish up the right arete.

name: Upper Block
description: Climb the east face of the block right above Smooth Operator.

name: Weasel Bite
description: On right side of Weasel warmup face head straight up the face starting left hand on the slopey rail feature in the middle of the face and right hand out on the arete.  Tricky.

name: Weasel in yo Pants
description: Left side of Weasel Warmup boulder.  Sit start by tree and do a tricky pull to crimps and top out up and right on big holds in the crack.  If you go direct up the face it is more sustained and according to reports better and checks in at a 4.

name: Weasel Left
description: Do the first move of What up Weasel and trend left around the corner.

name: Weasel Warmup
description: From a sit on the obvious break in the center of the wall move up and right into the juggy flake feature and topout.

name: What Up Weasel
description: Start sitting underneath the steep prow with your left hand on the arete and your right on a smallish, but good edge.  Hard move to the jug, some compression moves and trickery, and go up the face on good edges and slopers.  A weasel skittered right by us as we were working the problem.

name: A Slab Called Spot
description: From the nice jug climb up the center of the spotted and fun slab.  Probably the best warmup in the area and a good climb in general.

name: Don't Judge This Cover
description: A very fun little problem with a great second hold. Not dabbing is a hard part of the problem but the moves are worth a little effort to not dab all over the place.

name: Trifecta
description: Just left of a slab called spot on the arete above the weird landing.  Worth doing and pretty fun.

name: Ballistic
description: Start on the jug in the middle of the face and do a ballistic dyno to the lip and mantel.  A huge move.

name: Hot and Ready
description: Start as for Ballistic and do a huge move out right to an edge.  Then top it out.  A simple, short, and hard problem.

name: Chilldo
description: Right hand on jug, left hand underneath the arete on a nice juggy hold, pull on and do a campus move, then trick your way up the cool pink boulder.  A very good problem.

name: Cold Feet
description: Sit start on the left side of the boulder, hands low on obvious start holds. Slap your way up the slopers to top out the boulder. Pretty short route, but traversing further right before topping out adds some fun.

name: Green Slab
description: Climb up slab using crimps and side-pulls.

name: Weasel on Crack
description: Climb up large finger to hand size crack.  Tricky feet.

name: Close the Trenchcoat
description: Start sitting on the far left side of the El Parasol boulder, Left hand on the left arete, Right hand in a juggy sidepull undercling.  Do a cruxy deadpoint to a good hold and then do a deceptively tricky topout up and right.  Avoid the detached block at the top.  Or don't.  It just doesn't matter.  Pretty fun.

name: Drunchies
description: From a sit, with your left hand on a crimp and your right in an undercling, climb the Fridge.

name: El Parasol Project
description: Climb out the huge, steep roof on sloping ledges and small crimps.  Unlike most roofs at the lake, this actually has a few holds on it.

name: Expose Yourself
description: Climb the prominent nose like arete from a stand start on the El Parasol Boulder.  Feels exposed.

name: The Fridge direct
description: Start as for the fridge and go straight up.  Only a couple moves but fun.

name: The Fridge
description: A forced line, but good climbing.  Starting left hand on the lip and right hand underneath climb out the fridge feature and top out at the end.  Awesome and unique compression climbing.

name: Insidious
description: This is in the el parasol roof.  The start is pictured, link into Midwest Dream.  The big move on Midwest Dream is a bit heady, do be careful.

name: Miami Vice
description: From the obvious rail at the bottom of the roof and an edge just left of it, climb left into Vice Grip and finish as for that problem.  Likely the first V13 in Wisconsin and one of the hardest in the Midwest.

name: Midnight Snack
description: This is the obvious and difficult sit start on the Fridge Boulder.  With your right hand on an undercling and your left on a crimp, pull on and do a very powerful punch to a sloper.  From there finish it out on the Fridge Direct.

name: Midwest Dream
description: From a sit or crouch on the right side of the roof, with your right hand in a good slot and left on a low undercling, pull on and climb leftwards across the lip of the roof finishing on the left side of the far arete.  The seam 2 feet above the lip was not used so instead of mantling out early you climb out the whole feature.     This is definitely one of my favorite of the grade (whatever it ends up being) I have done at the lake.

name: Open Trenchcoat
description: Low start to Expose Yourself where you start squeezing both aretes underneath the nose in the roof.  Great moves, a scary landing though, with a drop off on one side and pointy rocks on the other.

name: Rubik's Cubicle
description: This climbs the overhanging dihedral-like boulder below the huge roof of the El Parasol project.  Start right hand on the big undercling/pinch, and left hand on a crimp just up and left.  Make a hard move up right to a jug and follow good holds to top out.

name: Vice Grip
description: Start on the left side of El Parasol roof, Left hand in an incut gaston and right hand on sidepull under the roof.  Move to the slopey lip, sort out your hands, then do some tenuous foot work and punch for a good hold.  Short, cool holds, and packs a punch.

name: The Vice is Right
description: Climb vice grip but continue right at the lip and finish up the arete.

name: Fat Raccoon
description: Starting right hand in the jug and left hand underneath the roof climb up and left encountering some tough moves along the way.  A low start is possible and will bump the difficulty up.

name: Fat Raccoon Sit aka Skinny Raccoon
description: Start on the low holds at the bottom of the roof and climb Fat Raccoon. The full line.

name: Fat Squirrel
description: Start sitting underneath the roof on low holds and do a few cool but dabby moves to the jug at chest level and then climb into squirrel arete.  Pretty fun.  If you start at the jug it is about v5 and good.

name: Squirrel Arete
description: Climb up the fridge like arete from a stand start.

name: The Grave Digger
description: Start with side-pull in middle of boulder.  Stab the thumbercling and set feet to turn it into an undercling.  Cross-over to slopey jug and top-out.

name: Grave of the Fallen
description: Start low on the left side of the boulder.  Move out to good crimp, and bump up arete enough to hit the good edge near the lip.  Top-out.

name: Fat Trick
description: From a sit on the arête left of Mixed Emotions starting crossed on low incut flakes on the left side of the arête climb into the finish of Mixed Emotions.  Nice moves and have a good spotter to make sure you don't fly off the boulder if you ping off.

name: Mixed Emotion
description: Classic?  You may doubt this, but yes.  It is.  Go try it.  Mike found and cleaned this beautiful line.  A sit start on crimps, an overhanging face with a discontinuous crack, and a scary topout.  What more could a Devil's Lake boulderer ask for?

name: Angry Squirrel
description: Just next to Snake Charmer, pull on the overhang from a stand above the hole, right hand on a cool incut crimper flake, left hand on a sidepull. Do a tough and committing feeling move to the lip and top out left or right.

name: Flash or Die
description: Climb the left side of the arete on the Glory or Death Boulder.  Really fun.

name: Glory or Death
description: Climb up the center of the downhill facing side of the Glory or Death Boulder from a stand on nice side pulls.  Great moves above a very poor landing.  If you have enough pads it's doable..

name: Jurassic World
description: Establish on under-cling and work your way up the thin face.

name: Monumental
description: Short burly compression arete on Glory or Die Boulder.  Start crouching, and slap up the refridgerator like arete.  Short but good moves, cool topout.

name: Snake Charmer
description: Start sitting kind of awkwardly on low good holds, do a hard pull to the nice flat big hold, and do some tricky and powerful moves up the blunt arete to good holds at the top.  Great moves

name: Trump Bucks
description: Kinda fun.. Sit start the short overhanging arete with a sidepull for the left hand and right on the arete on a pretty good spot.  Grade may differ depending on method..:)

name: What What!
description: Start on 2 crimps.  Move left into an undercling and trick your way up the face.

name: Broken warm-up
description: Start on two really good edges and cross through to large block.  Follow block to top.

name: Talus Walker
description: Start with good jug on the right.  Paste feet and gun up arete for good hold.  Slap out left to crack and mantle up.  Fun

name: Two Face
description: From a sit start climb the pretty arete above the less than perfect landing.  I started left hand on a downpulling triangle hold, right hand on a low juggy sidepull.  Tough to tell if this is hard or more scary than hard.

name: Awesome Blossom
description: Start from a sit with a right crimp and a thin left sidepull.  Gain a slopey hold for the left hand, bust big right to an incut hold and finish it up.

name: Stanage Arete
description: Pretty fun hanging arete problem with some dynamic moves and a fun top out.      Start left hand on a pinch under the roof, and right hand on either a triangular ledge, or a slot/pinch type hold.  Big move left around the corner, then a fun, sequency top section.    There's also a potential low start using an undercling in the roof, and a crimp on the arete.

name: Big Red
description: From the right on a pedestal climb up the beautiful slab.  Amazing and exposed climbing over a terrible landing.  The crux is at the top.  Could be easier but don't want to sandbag this one.  I checked it out on a rope first.

name: Chip and Dales
description: Start on obvious low edges.  Climb the short steep face.

name: Ride the Lightning
description: From a low start, climb the obvious arete to the right of Big Red.

name: Coldplay
description: Start on obvious double crimps at chest height.  Climb up arete to knife edge topout.

name: Finding Remo
description: Start right on arete sloper and left on huge undercling, make your way up slopey arete to topout on the knife edge as per Coldplay.

name: Double Mint
description: Sit start in pit with side pull for left hand and crimp for right work up shallow dihedral with a couple of incuts to juggy top out. Would be better if it were taller.

name: Dorsal Fin
description: In the cave, start siting squeezing the arête with a left sloper and right low pinch.  Climb the arête through fins and blocky holds to escape the cave.

name: Fairy Tale
description: Start sitting with a right sidepull and faint left sidepull.  A crux first move leads to fun and easier climbing to the apex of the arête.

name: The Fox Hole
description: Start with left hand on sloppy pinch and right hand on bulge just right of undercling. Then continue to slap up the side until you can get a high foot for desperate move to top out.

name: Outsmart the Fox
description: SDS with left hand pinch and right sloper.  Compress and push your way up arete to tenuous mantle.      Pics coming soon...

name: What does the fox say?
description: Sit start on a blocky feature with a foot out right. Pull a technical mantle and then run up the shallow slab.

name: Good Touch
description: Getting started is the hard park. Get your right hand on the best part of the lip and heel hook with your right. Move out to a awesome hold on the face and follow the lip to the top. Fun stuff!

name: Juicy Fruit
description: Stand start on the left side and traverse the lip with a couple of face holds for right hand. Good holds on top though covered in bird bombs

name: McMantle
description: Grab the lip.  Mantle.  A lower start would be possible but is hard and quite dabby.

name: Hot Wing
description: From a sit, w/ your left hand in an undercling and your right on and edge, using the detached block for your feet move right to a gaston, then do a long pull through to better holds, then the top.

name: Scapularis
description: From good holds down and left pull on and climb up the cool arete feature.  Take care on some of the holds and the spike on the arete.

name: Shoo Fly
description: Sit start on a crimp and jug on the lip with a heel hook.  Work your way up the arete on nice slopers/sloper jugs and top out.  Face still requires some heavy cleaning.

name: Bitch Better Have My Money
description: start right hand  on a good edge and left hand on a slopey edge. Use some trickery to move into no fall territory where you make a couple more moves before traversing the lip up and right.

name: Pimp slap
description: Start on an obvious jug, make a big move to a sloper, negotiate some more slopers and top out.

name: Sir Slap Alot
description: Start standing on the left side of the face and follow the slopey lip up and right and topout as for Smackdown.  Fun.

name: Smackdown
description: Start standing right hand on the big sidepull/undercling feature and left hand undercling.  Do a fun long move and then an interesting mantel.

name: Smackdown Sit
description: Start sitting squeezing the feature, do a tough slap cross over move and power through to the top of Smackdown.

name: Step Left
description: Start as for Watch Your Step but immediately step left and wander up the slab.

name: Watch Your Step
description: Starting left on a good hold follow the lip right above the pit, and the slab, and top out.  Fun moves and a little scary.

name: The Great Eye
description: A great slab problem. Few holds on a near perfect slab. This ride might have a height requirement! Awesome slot hold near the top that looks like a eye!!

name: The Walrus
description: From a sit on the left side of the downhill face, with your left hand on an edge on the left side of the arete, and your right on a block pinch, trend right, staying low through edges.  Gain a crack and wrap around the corner.. and keep wrapping until you hit the north arete and top out.  Long and pumpy, and it would be tough or scary to top out earlier.

name: Whale's Tail
description: From a sit climb up the compression arete out of the hole.  Fun.  Dabby for sure.

name: Aunt Milli
description: Start standing on sidepull crimps. Use detached bit for feet. Go up the vertical to slabby face using the crack and ledges to the left if you like. Trend right for top out.

name: Castle in the Sky
description: Start seated on a block down and right.  Make a big move into a good flake then trend left across the face.  Top out and and run up the high but easy slab.

name: Haunted Castle
description: Start same as Castle in the Sky, but from the jug on the left arete, instead of going straight up, continue traversing left over the slanted landing and top out on the far southwest corner of the boulder up a handcrack.

name: Hobama Care
description: Start from a sit on the right side of the shield-like wall, with your left hand on a good sidepull, and right low on the arete.  Pull on, bust a move with your right, then pop out left and compress.  Squeeze up the shield, encountering a crimp, then an easing top out.  The crack out left was not used.  Climb the cool feature!

name: Apples and Bananas
description: Start on two opposing crimps/rails on a small buldge with good feet.  Make a big move to a lip sloper, shuffle feet and gain better holds on the top slab/face.  Top out.

name: Dry Spot
description: Start with good right hand and heel hook. Bump up to good left hold then make a big move around the right arete and pop to the top

name: Low Hanging Fruit
description: Start on a good sidepull rail and climb up the arete through a couple moves on very cool edges and pinches.

name: Peaches
description: Start low with left hand on a crimp rail and right hand on an undercling. Climb out the bulge and up the boulder.

name: Strawberry Jam
description: Start on the right side of the boulder on an obvious ledge / pocket.  move left through crimps, crossing over peaches. Finish on the upper left side of the boulder.

name: Strawberry Peach Pie
description: Same start position as Strawberry Jam. Bump to the crimp out left then either move your right hand to a side pull or crimp before bumping up to the large sloper hold on Peaches and top out above.

name: Trouser Snaker
description: Start as for Low Hanging Fruit, matched on a right facing sidepull.  Pull on (without the blocks for feet), make a long move right to a pinch, sort your feet, move through a crimp and another cool pinch, then finish right on better holds above Apples and Bananas.  You BETTER not dab on that tree.

name: Twerk Life
description: On the right side of the left of the fruit boulders, start from a sit on good edges right next to each other.  Move left through a small edge with a sharp thumb catch, then go huge left to a gaston feature and take it to the top.  This is essentially a link up of Apples and Bananas and Low Hanging Fruit.  A foot on the kicker was used, but not the detached blocks.

name: Audacity
description: SDS under the overhang. Right hand on the lip and left hand on a perfect crimp in the crack. Get a high right heel hook (you've been going to yoga, right?) and you're off. Fun moves through a bulge over the lip and an unusually grippy top-out.    The crux is probably finding a spot for your tush, followed by the heel hook. After that, it's party time.

name: Creaker
description: Go up creaky holds in the center of the Nature Walk face.  Good movement on kinda sketchy holds.  Be careful, the landing is weird.

name: Exposed
description: On the Left side of the Nature Walk Face.  From a stand start at the bottom of the slab ramp follow the Left trending seam around the corner above the drop off and top out as for Like a Boss and Group Leader.

name: Group Leader
description: Starts on the good rail for your right hand and a crimp for your left.  Slap your way up each side and end it with a nice heel hook to the finishing jug.

name: Insomnia
description: Awesome tall line up the tallest part of the face with the crux about 2/3 the way up, squeezing up a mini bulge. There is a committing throw to the lip. Really fun climbing.

name: Jug Life
description: Fun jugs on the right side of the Nature Walk face.

name: Like a Boss
description: Start on a good slopey right hand sidepull and left hand on downpulling sloper.  Go directly up the right arete of Group Leader using a series of bump moves possibly and punch to the jug.  Fun.  Essentially the same start as group leader.

name: Little Arete
description: From a sit start on low good holds do a few fun moves and topout.

name: Seams Fun
description: From a sit work up fun seams and balance your way to the top.  A fun line.  The stands a little easier and fun too.

name: Six Feet Under
description: Start on the rail in the pit, move up crimps to get to a bomber incut crimp (avoid the broken flake). Finish up towards the right. Height will certainly be an advantage.

name: Celebrity Jeopardy
description: Start to the left on two crimps with good feet.    Work your way right and up. Big finish move to a massive jug.   Super crimpy, but fun.

name: Bride of the Fox
description: Stand start on two slopey edges and climb directly up the technical slab. Execute the high crux and better holds await you above.

name: Happy-Go Highball
description: Climb up south facing corner of tall boulder.

name: Pale Blue Dot
description: Start on the jug rail and continue up through two more amazing rail features. Finish directly up the airy slab. An awesome climb, in my opinion. Much trickier than it looks.

name: Troubadour
description: Start matched on a jug under the roof, climb out the roof to the right and compress your way to a crack system on the headwall that leads to the topout.

name: Fauxnetics
description: Start matched on the rail jug, traverse out left, top out

name: Hidden Treasure
description: Start with slopey right hand ledge and nice left hand side pull. Work your way up the face. If you use the arete this climb will be easier.

name: Reign of Giants
description: Start in the middle of this large boulder on a set of jugs. Work your way up and left on delicate crimp moves. Top out at the point. There is a possible lower start to this, it might make it slightly harder.

name: Rise of the Hobbits
description: Start low and right on good edge, this is a sit start to Reign Of Giants. Hardest Part of the climb is keeping your butt off the rock in the middle of the climb. Here is a beta video if you are so inclined vimeo.com/171149136

name: X Marks the Spot
description: From a sit, climb the beautiful left arete, topout.

name: Master Gardener
description: Start in the pit with 2 blocky ledge hands right next to each other, and trick your way up the overhanging face.

name: The Nothing Roof Project
description: Climb up and out blank roof.

name: Supple Slab
description: Climb slab with big moves on somewhat suspect flakes.

name: Butter Knife
description: Start crouched with a very biter undercling for the left hand and a crimp sidepull around the right of the arête for the right hand.  Climb the arête.

name: The Subtle Knife
description: Stand start - left hand sidepull, right hand small crimp. Climb technical moves up the slightly overhanging face.

name: Fearful Symmetry
description: Formerly the "Crack of Doom" project.  Begin with your left hand in the crack and right hand on a jug sidepull.  Make an easy move before diving into five moves of powerful yet technical climbing.  A committing layback move guards the lip.  Proud!

name: Death of a Traveling Salesman
description: Starting the same as Massive Vertigo and then head right. This line will take you straight up the boulder but over terrible landing that is hard to protect.

name: Massive Vertigo
description: Start on the crimp rail towards the bottom of the pit and climb up and left to the sloper on the arete.  Go up from here.    Ed:  Originally given V8, new/easier beta has been found (see below-- sweaty's video is him doing the original V8).

name: Peter's Corner
description: Start on large ledge near left corner, climb up corner to gain good face holds.  Top-out on slopers and some ok in-cuts.     Starting on lower crimps makes it a bit harder, maybe V2/3, but it's not as fun.

name: So Dope
description: Sit start low with slopey crimps, bump up to sloper and toss out right to good edge near sloper on Massive Vertigo.  Stay tight and gain small crimp, top-out same as MV.

name: So Dope Direct
description: Starts on same 2 low crimps as So Dope, moves up to match on sloper, and then straight up face.  Given V8 originally, some new beta makes it some easier.  Ian's original beta is still very hard.

name: Astral Projection
description: Start low on the arete and climb up and out slab.

name: Cranium
description: Start sitting, left hand on the blunt arête, right on an undercling pinch with a definitive thumb catch. Go up and right to mantle, and finish with an easy slab.

name: Eclipse
description: Start as per Tunder Tighs, finish on Full Moon rising.  If you use the jugs as per Tunder Tighs to finish, you have officially cheated. Mantle it out..

name: Fixie
description: Goes up the right side of the "Hipsters V5" boulder. Start on the juggy sidepulls and get a heel hook up right. Power straight up through a series of jugs/slopers to top it out.  Thuggy!

name: Fontesque
description: Start underneath the arete with left hand on a toothlike hold and right on a pinch undercling.  Climb the arete with balance, gain the obvious holds on the face and top out.  This is also on here as the impossiproject.

name: Full Moon Rising
description: Start hands low in horizontal break, up and over bulge to slab on small holds to topout.

name: The Hipsters V5
description: Climb starts in pit on good side pull with left hand and good right hand. Harder first couple moves then a pumpy arete. V3 start out of the pit and just do the arete.

name: Nausea
description: Start the same as "Tunder Tighs" and climb directly up the face with a small pit underneath you..  Formerly the "Big Boy Project"

name: Prow
description: From bellow steep bulge, start on large ledge and gain upper section of bulge.  Top-out.  Super cool!

name: Puke, Master-flash
description: Start left hand on good ledge and jump for right hand edge.  Get your feet on and move up boulder with a big cross-over move to a jug.  Powerful moves and props to Aaron for this contribution.    Starting lower with both hand below is still an awesome open project.

name: Remo's Sacrifice
description: Super proud!  Stand start with steep arete and gain sloper.  Toss out right to good hold and hike up to small crimps above the lip.  Finish move is super committing.   A sit start should be added for full value and added difficulty, but the holds were too wet for us to try.

name: Tunder Tighs
description: Start left hand on good edge and right hand on pinch rail. Using some tensiony heel hooks and compression, make huge moves up to the lip then up and over.

name: Thick Dawg
description: In the uphill facing cave, start with a downpulling three finger slopey crimp pinch, and a biter pinch edge for the left (see photo). With difficulty climb out the cave.  A thin “blubber” pad would be nice, as it is a bit dabby.  The cave keeps the temps down and it is tricky and powerful.

name: Blair's Arete
description: Start low and right on boulder with left hand on arete and right in a slot.  Climb arete to fun top-out.

name: Call of the Wild
description: Climb up the center of the north face of the elbow room boulder starting from a stand with your right hand in a good slanting slot and your left on an undercling.. The first move is deceptively tricky..

name: Elbow Room
description: Start with right hand in slot and left on crimp.  Set left foot and gun for pocket.  A couple more big moves get you to a heady top-out.  Fun!

name: High Room
description: Same start as High-Low.  At good edge, bump out to pocket and finish up on Elbow Room.  Fun link-up!

name: The High-Low
description: Start low on jug.  Hike feet and gun big for good edge.  Bump out to slopers and find hidden left crimp.  Top-out.

name: Manta Ray
description: A pure line, definitely cool, and very unique.  Start hanging from the edge near the arete and surmount the hanging block feature. Hint: We campused left for the first move and threw a heal hook..

name: Mike's Green Fantasy
description: Start low and left on boulder.  Bump left hand up to small crack and ease up to slopers.  Traverse right along slopey jugs to big finish.

name: Super Warbler
description: Start about 5ft. to the left of the Warbler and move across boulder via pocket and foot trickery to finish on the Warbler.  Really cool moves and adds a lot to the existing line.

name: The Warbler
description: Start under roof with right hand jug and left had pinch.  Set feet and make a big move to a good edge.  Move right through pinches and slopers to top-out.   Really fun movement!

name: Whetstone
description: Stand start on the obvious sloper rail. Climb up the steep wall to a crux topout.

name: 5th Grade Oboe
description: A wonderful beginner's offwidth, this climb sits starts on the obvious hold on the left side of the crack. Although you can get away with entering the crack later, the top out requires some amount of crack trickery. Prepare yourself for a full body workout.

name: Accordion Left
description: Same start as the Accordian but move left immediately to the slab.  Fun and a little tricky.

name: The Accordion
description: Start matched on a sharpish, incut edge on the left arete.  Move right one way or the other and compress up the feature. A sweet overhanging squeeze problem!

name: The Asonga
description: Start low with right hand on arete and left on small side-pull.  Move up to good left edge and top-put.  Finding the good feet is the trick.

name: Broken Reed Crack
description: Sit start on a good right-hand foot with some okay finger jams. Have a good time jamming fingers then head left for a funky try-not-to-dab mantle. Would be great except for the weird top-out, however the landing is great.

name: The Cellist
description: Sit start with opposing, three finger pocket side pulls.  Climb the striking little arete on cool holds to an engaging finish.  Super fun.

name: The Didgeridoo
description: Stand start on the large flake. Cool compression moves lead up the blunt arete. Detached blocks are not used.

name: The Dulcimer
description: A drop off problem but really freaking cool.. Start on a ledge left of the very obvious, super clean arete with a large sidepull jug.  Gain the arete with huge feet, and with difficulty transfer around it and get the jug break.  Traverse off or drop from there.

name: Mandatory Recorder
description: This is an easy route that's good for a warmup, or if someone needs to get used to quartzite. Don't use the arete on the right to make it more interesting.Start with undercling down left and pull a few moves to get your feet up onto the face, then haul over the top.

name: Tom Tom
description: From below roof, start with left hand on block and right on side-pull. Pull on and move up to slopey lip. Top out.

name: The Tuba
description: Sort of cool.. Start with left hand on slopey edge, right on side pull.  A few power strange moves gains easier climbing.  Once on jugs 8/10 feet up you are good to drop or downclimb.  Not an eliminate per say, but it does only climb the bulging arete feature.

name: Tutu Slab
description: An excellent slab, slightly technical for the grade. The right-hand arete is off. Starts balancey and fun, holds get better and then great towards the top. Sit start on some combination of the lowest holds, obvious start is matched on the vertical seam with left-hand sidepulls.  Exit straight up and then walk/scramble all the way to the end for the V0 downclimb. Consider adding a pad for the downclimb.

name: Winnie The Tu
description: Start sitting low and right of the arete and then have fun slapping up the steadily improving arete. Landing has a sloping angle so spotters are best downhill to protect from the pit just around the corner. If you're already here for the slab you've gotta check this one out!

name: Archaic Conception
description: Start on the edge from a stand in the middle of the pretty slab.  Move left to better holds and continue up fun moves.

name: B.I.A.
description: Start on the jug.  Climb the arete and face feature.  A fun and awesome problem that stays on you until the end.

name: The Believer
description: From the edge at chest level in the middle of the pretty slab, move right, gaining a pod slot, and continue up through better holds.  Don’t use the other wall to the right.  Pretty tricky and one of those v3’s that could give you a run for your money..

name: Cool Alert
description: Start sitting, left hand with a low downpulling flat edge, and right with a low incut sidepull.  Climb up and left, traverse across the face through a rail, gain the other arete and top out the slab above the slanting landing.

name: Edge of the Earth
description: Start on the large jug feature near the center of the face and work straight up using small crimps and sidepulls. About halfway up, I trended to the right arete and finished up around the corner (without using the detached blocks). Staying true to the center is a project waiting to be done.

name: Flat Earth Project
description: From the incut rail, climb the center of the slab.

name: Call of the Child
description: Obvious blocky jug line left of the Canine. Follow the cracks and blocks up to the top

name: The Canine
description: This thin and slabby climb follows the face up the canine shaped boulder. From a stand or sit work your way to a good ledge. Balance, mantle, crimp, or will yourself up to a high hold and topout.Left blocky holds and right arete are both offThe positive crimps and low angle make this a satisfying puzzle to solve. Must do for this area!

name: Canis Lupus
description: Canis Lupus - The Wolf  Sit start with left hand in a triangle ledge and right in small crimp. Climb the face up to a good horizontal break. Find small holds and high feet to an airy mantle finish. This stays consistent at the grade and isnt over until you're on top.  Channel your inner wolf and send those final moves !

name: The Howling
description: From a jug, climb the pillar on good holds for the most part.  There is a long reach at the top.  Take care, a fall near the top could be very bad.

name: Lone Wolf
description: Start sitting on a ledge, with an inverted diamond pinch for the left hand and punchy edge for the right. Move left, pull through a couple cruxy moves, then wrap left around the arete and up.  The top is pretty easy but a fall might be weird with a boulder behind you.

name: Pack Mentality
description: From good holds right of the arete, climb to a jug, then commit to an airy sequence that uses the arete, high off the ground, to easing, but delicate and serious climbing up high.  A proud and incredible line.

name: Timberwolf Arete
description: Super obvious arete climb as you enter the corridor proper. Start sitting with a good jug shelf and a left hand undercling jug.  Sequence up to a good break and then up even higher. Top out is easy

name: Wolf Arete
description: From a sit on the left side of the arete, climb it.

name: Wolf Paw
description: Arete left of Lone Wolf from a sit.  Same Boulder, in the corridor. Start with your left hand on the arete and right with a pinchy edge.  You will probably finish with the same mantle as Lone Wolf.  Technical slab compression climbing.

name: Blarney
description: Climb the arete from a stand, with a sidepull for the left hand to start.  A little tricky and pretty darn fun.  This boulder is a good warm up option for the area.

name: Kitty
description: Start sitting on a boulder, in a groove, right hand on the arete, left wide on a pinch.  Climb straight up.  Kinda good and a little tricky.

name: Ripley
description: Start sitting at the base of the shortish, slabby wall, with a sidepull for the right and a good, kinda hollow flake for the left.  Gain a slanting, slopey rail then get the lip and mantle.

name: Bene Gesserit
description: Start matched low under roof on the big side-pulling jug using the detached block underneath for feet, pull a few long moves on good holds and top out up and right over the slab.

name: Dune
description: Start matched on the very low left jug in the roof.  With difficulty and trickery, establish and hopefully send. Essentially the problem Gene Besserit with out the giant detached block. Formerly the Toehook Dream Project.

name: Gom Jabbar
description: Start sitting left hand under roof on large sidepull and right hand on a good ledge on the right face. Pull on and and grab some awesome pinches near the arete, continue left along the lip and top out the same as Bene Gesserit.

name: Missionaria Protectiva
description: Sit start to Gom Jabbar. Start sitting left hand on a sidepull in the center of the roof and right hand on the arete. Pull hard into a compression knee bar (knee pad might be necessary) on right and toe hook at the base of the roof. Climb right into the start of Gom Jabbar and top out the same as Bene Gesserit.

name: Joan of Arc
description: This is the left arete of the Joan of Arc slab. Start on a good side pull and crimp with great feet. Cruise the arete to some tricky footwork and a beautiful topout.

name: Mary Queen of Scots
description: Start on the far right traverse rail and climb into the center crack. Follow a series of ledges and crimps to a ledge but heady top out.

name: Massive Attack
description: A very long problem and pretty fun.  Start in corridor on jugs.  Climb up and right above jumbled boulders, crossing a crack system then continue right and up the face.

name: Teardrop
description: B side.. Start sitting, left hand on the arete, right out wide on a slick sidepull.  With difficulty somehow gain the jug above and top out. For cool points do Massive Attack then do this as a second pitch.

name: A Quiet Place
description: Climb the right side of the arete from a stand.  Take care not to miss the pedestal if you fall.  I down climbed just right of the line back to the pedestal, which is much easier than the climb but very airy, which is why I gave it the x rating.

name: Gangnam Style
description: Stand start with a thin crimp at the 6 foot level left of the arête and a low, thin undercling right of the arête.  With difficulty, pull on, gain the lip then head up and right to finish.

name: Intrigue
description: The far right line on the One Word Boulder.  Start right hand above your head on a two finger crimp and left lower on a pinch or undercling hold with a good ledge for the feet.  Climb up.  A lower start is undone.

name: Mystique
description: From a right undercling and left sidepull, bust a long move up the arête feature to a gaston.  Tricky moves lead to an easing finish.

name: Rogue
description: Start with a three finger edge for the right hand and a very obvious pinch/ slopey crimp next to it.  Bust left to another pinch and continue leftwards, gaining a jug and a crimpy bulge/slab encounter.

name: Rogue Direct Project
description: From the start of Rogue (a three finger edge for the right, and a pinch just next to it for the left) climb the center of the over hanging face, likely pinching arete features.  This will be good and quite hard.

name: Vanilla Ice
description: Start sitting, with a low left juggy sidepull and a low right sidepull on the arête around the same level.  Climb the arête.

name: Darkest Before Dawn
description: A B side for sure.  Though kinda cool:). Start with a undercling for the left, and a sidepull for the right. Dyno to a jug and finish up the arete.  Sunset arete (v2) is the obvious left arete, listed in a different area.  This could use some sorting.

name: Sunset Arete
description: Start low on jug and climb right leaning arete to apex.  On the same boulder as Darkest Before Dawn.  50 feet south of Gom Jabar at about the same level on the hillside though barely lower.

name: Apocalypto
